{ With the symmetry on the king's side, I believe black's best attempt at a better game is to gain space on the king's side and then place his knight in a position where it can out-value the white bishops. This provides two ideas to the position: 14. ...g5 which secures a square on e5 for the knight and 14. ...h5 which secures f5 for the knight's eventual need for value. }
